properties.areaDesc: North Coast; Admiralty Inlet Area; Central Coast
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 6 at 9:29PM PST until February 8 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Admiralty Inlet Area, North Coast and Central Coast.

* WHEN...From Friday afternoon through Saturday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power
lines. Widespread power outages are possible. Travel could be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Widespread west winds are expected along
the coast. For the east entrance of the Strait of Juan de Fuca
and Island County, expect a rapid increase in west winds to
arrive during the overnight hours Friday night.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING
